Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pour a good glug of oil onto a #baking tray{} (to completely cover the bottom) and pop into your oven. Peel the @potatoes{450%g}(peeled), chop them into 3cm chunks. Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{5-6%minutes} or until the edges have softened when you poke them with a #knife{}.

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan and give your pan a shake to fluff them up. Next, sprinkle on the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and toss to coat. Take your hot baking tray out of the oven, carefully transfer your potatoes onto it in a single layer, turning in the oil. Season the potatoes with @salt{pinch}, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, lay the slices of @Serrano ham{2%slices} lengthways on a #board{} (1 slice per chicken breast). Place the @British chicken breasts{2} horizontally across the middle. Wrap the ham around the chicken to enclose it. Place them seam-side down on a large, lightly-oiled baking tray (we'll add the broccoli to the tray later on). Repeat with the remaining chicken and ham. Drizzle a little oil over the chicken, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-28%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). When the chicken is halfway through cooking, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} to the chicken #baking tray{}, drizzle with oil and spread out in a single layer. Season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{}, then pop back in your oven for the remaining ~{12-15%minutes}.

While everything cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a small #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the shallot and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally. Pour in the @water{100.5%ml} and stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil and simmer until the liquid has reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{100%g}, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} if you feel it needs it.

Once the chicken has cooked, transfer to a board to rest for ~{2-3%minutes}. Reheat the sauce if necessary. Serve the chicken on plates with the cheesy potatoes and broccoli alongside. Sprinkle the @truffle zest{1} over the potatoes and drizzle over the sauce. Enjoy!